    "description": "The Deaf World Cup 2027 is more than a sporting event—it is a global mission field. As Deaf athletes, coaches, families, and fans from around the world gather for this premier international competition, an unprecedented opportunity will emerge to share the hope of Christ with people from dozens of nations and cultures. Volunteers will have the chance to build friendships, encourage competitors, engage in meaningful conversations, and share their faith through sign language and personal connection. For many Deaf individuals, access to the Gospel, Scripture, and Christian discipleship resources in their heart language is extremely limited. The Deaf World Cup creates a rare moment when thousands of Deaf people can be reached in one place with the love of Jesus. Whether serving through hospitality, sports outreach, prayer, or relationship-building, participants can help make an eternal impact among one of the world's largest unreached people groups. Come be part of a once-in-a-generation opportunity to take the Gospel to the nations—through the global Deaf community gathered at the Deaf World Cup 2027. This is one of several groups that will go either before the event, during the event, or after the event."
